+// Package scopefilter implements Deckhouse's cross-namespace scope-filtering
+// mechanism: `kubectl get <resource> -A --scope=<accessible|user|system|project:<name>>`
+// returns the subset of a namespaced resource the caller can see instead of a
+// flat 403, without changing default `-A` semantics for anyone who does not
+// ask for it.
+//
+// The mechanism generalizes an existing, narrower patch that gave this
+// behavior only to `namespaces` (see pkg/registry/core/namespace/storage,
+// which now builds on this package with identity field "metadata.name" and
+// an unconditional trigger instead of a header). Generic namespaced resources
+// (built-in, via storage_<group>.go, and CustomResourceDefinitions, via
+// apiextensions-apiserver's customresource_handler.go) use identity field
+// "metadata.namespace" and a header-gated trigger.
+//
+// Security invariant (do not weaken without re-reading the design note this
+// patch ships against): the RBAC safety floor added whenever the
+// authorization filter bypassed a 403 for this request MUST always be
+// AccessibleNamespaces() ∩ BulkSubjectAccessReview(group, resource, verb) --
+// narrowed by the *actual* (resource, verb) of the request being served,
+// never a plain "has access to something, somewhere" check. A looser floor
+// lets a caller with e.g. `get secrets` rights in namespace N see unrelated
+// resources in N via --scope=system/user/project, despite having no RBAC for
+// them at all.
+package scopefilter
